Hypervisor
----------
It is a software that creates and runs virtual machines(VMs)

How Hypervisor works:
---------------------
Virtualbox share hardware resources from Host OS
Seperate set of virtual CPU,RAM,storage etc.
VMs are fully isolated(independent of hosted OS)

Benefits of VMs:
----------------
We don't need new resources to use different OS
No risk of any issues with your primary OS
Testing any app on different OS

Virtualisation uses:
--------------------
Cheap
Reduces workload,space and energy
Easy backup using snapshot
Easy recovery